gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 112, Spurs 102
gameRecap.excerpt: Golden State defeats San Antonio, 112-102. For Golden State, Jonathan Kuminga led the way with 22 points and five rebounds while aided by Klay Thompson (21 points, four 3PM) and Chris Paul (19 points, nine rebounds, eight assists) in the victory. Victor Wembanyama finished with 27 points (three 3PM), 14 rebounds, and two blocks with Devin Vassell tallying 17 points (five 3PM) for San Antonio in the losing effort. Golden State improves to 34-30, while San Antonio moves to 14-51 in the loss.
